content:
Launch an Angular or LWC OmniScript from the OmniScript Action element on a FlexCard. For example, launch a form that updates Account information based on the account ID passed from the FlexCard to the OmniScript.

From the FlexCard Designer, drag an Action element into a state.
Select OmniScript as the action type if a FlexCard is used in Experience Cloud.
Click OmniScript, and select the OmniScript that you want to launch.
If needed, you can select the VisualForce page where you want to show the OmniScript.

To update the OmniScript's layout, select Lightning or Newport as the layout type.
Enter the sObject's context ID associated with your OmniScript.
For example, if your OmniScript updates account information, your context ID is an account record ID variable from the data source, such as {AccountId}.

If you selected an LWC OmniScript in the Console Tab Label field, enter the visible label of the console tab.
If you selected an LWC OmniScript, from Console Tab Icon, select the icon that you want to show on the subtab of a console after the OmniScript Action link is clicked.

To pass contextual data as a key/value pair, perform these steps:
Click + Add New next to Input Parameters.
In Key, enter a variable name with the prefix omniscript__.
If needed, indicate whether to open the OmniScript on the current tab or on a new tab.

You can configure the options that are common for all action properties. See FlexCards Action Properties.

Whatâ€™s next: To style your action element, click Style. See FlexCards Action Style Properties.

Launch an OmniScript from an OmniScript Action on a FlexCard in Lightning Experience
On a Lightning Experience page, launch an OmniScript from an OmniScript Action on a FlexCard.
Launch an OmniScript from an OmniScript Action on a FlexCard in Experience Cloud

To pass data from an LWC OmniScript to an embedded FlexCard, perform these steps:
Pass Data from an LWC OmniScript to an Embedded FlexCard.

OmniStudio Standard now supports OmniScripts launched from FlexCards in Experience Builder. With the OmniScript for Experience Builder component, you can load a dynamic OmniScript launched from a FlexCard Action element into an Experience Cloud page.
title: Launching Scripts from FlexCards in OmniStudio
